def: The act of viewing; a look. [Obs.]
A bird having lobate toes; esp., a phalarope.
Of or pertaining to a uvula.
The act or practice of jesting. [Obs.]

Belonging to the hyacinth; resemblingthe hyacinth; in colorlike the hyacinth. Milton.His curling locks like hyacinthine flowers. Cowper.The hyacinthine boy, for whom Morn well might break and April bloom.Emerson.
To lay on, as the hands, in the religious rites of confirmationand ordination.
That which jets out or projects from anything. [R.] H. Miller.

That which is seized by violence or obtained by robbery,especially collective spoil taken in war; plunder; pillage. Milton.To play booty, to play dishonestly, with an intent to lose; to allowone's adversary to win at cards at first, in order to induce him tocontinue playing and victimize him afterwards. [Obs.] L'Estrange.
To name; to mention; to utter. [Obs.]As oft I heard my lord them neven. Chaucer.
